o not currently have nearly the clean energy capacity to fully replace foss=
il fuel usage and we&#8217;ll likely need breakthrough innovations in some =
combination of nuclear, solar, wind, fusion, hydrogen, and battery technolo=
gies to fully replace fossil fuels on the schedule that we want to. </p><p =
